				<div class="faqs-question">
					<h4>How should I have yoggie?</h4>
				</div>
				<div class="faqs-answer">
					<p>However you like! Most yoggsters blitz into a drink then have immediately or put into thermos/shaker for later. Many blend with less water for a thicker (yoghurt like) texture and eat from bowl, sprinkled with fresh fruit, nuts, seeds, granola for crunch.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faqs-right-content">
				<div class="faqs-question">
					<h4>Can I have yoggie instead of a meal?</h4>
				</div>
				<div class="faqs-answer">
					<p>Absolutely. Yoggie is designed as a tastier, quicker and (much) healthier breakfast, lunch or dinner.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="faqs-right-content">
				<div class="faqs-question">
					<h4>What is in a yoggie?</h4>
				</div>
				<div class="faqs-answer">
					<p>Yoggie recipes contain between seven and twenty four 100% natural ingredients to make them taste great and give you exactly the right balance of carbs, protein and good fats. Most have each of the following:</br>
					<strong>Fruit</strong> - for tangy sweetness and micronutrient hit</br>
					<strong>Milled seeds</strong> - for a bit of crunch plus omega 3 and omega 6 (great for head and heart)</br>
					<strong>Grain</strong> - for texture & crunch and slow-release carbs to keep you going longer</br>
					<strong>Superfoods</strong> - natural superfood pellets to cram each yoggie with goodness</br>
					<strong>Natural protein source</strong> - to give your body what it needs to function and suppress hunger pangs</br>
					<strong>Vegetable</strong> - to balance sweetness of fruit and give you lots of natural vitamins & minerals</br>
					<strong>Good fats sources</strong> - such as nuts/avocado turn taste to 11 and provide omega 9 (hormone helpers!)</p>
				</div>
			</div>
